## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 61](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section61&num=0&edition=prelim) defines gross income broadly: compensation for services, interest, dividends, rents, royalties, business income, gains from property, and so on. Wages were translated at the prior stage; this stage collects the other income components your AGI will need.

