The non-wage income picked up here is:

- Ordinary dividends ([Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 3b): **{{ side.ordinary_dividends_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Qualified dividends ([Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 3a, taxed at preferential rates per § 1(h)): **{{ side.qualified_dividends_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Interest income ([Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 2b): **{{ side.interest_income_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Capital gain distributions reported on 1099-DIV box 2a: **{{ side.capital_gain_distributions_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Substitute payments in lieu of dividends (1099-MISC box 8 / 1099-B box 1f): **{{ side.substitute_payments_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
{# IRS-VERIFIED 2026-05-12 — 2025 Schedule 1 (Form 1040) fields 8/9/10 (Other income / Total other income / additional income to Form 1040) against https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1040s1.pdf #}
- Staking rewards or other Schedule 1 line 8 income: **{{ side.staking_income_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Schedule 1 line 9 / line 10 other income totalled: **{{ side.schedule_1_other_income_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

These flow into AGI at US25-07; the qualified-dividend portion also drives the preferential-rate worksheet at US25-09.

